<subSubSection id="7DEE653F5698FF2CD21AFC6AFE7C6422" lastPageId="133" lastPageNumber="133" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="354B36B45698FF2DD21AFC6AFBF066DF" blockId="132.[801,1095,904,928]" box="[801,1095,904,928]" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">
<heading id="6E0381D85698FF2DD21AFC6AFBF066DF" box="[801,1095,904,928]" centered="true" fontSize="9" level="2" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" reason="2">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD255FC6AFBF066DF" authority="Gray, 1831" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[878,1095,904,928]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD255FC6AFC7D66E0" box="[878,970,904,927]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Lasiurus</emphasis>
Gray, 1831
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B45698FF2CD3F7FC5BFE7C6422" blockId="132.[684,1213,953,1738]" lastBlockId="133.[108,636,226,646]" lastPageId="133" lastPageNumber="133" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">
The systematics of 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD2ADFC58FC4666AE" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[918,1009,954,977]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD2ADFC58FC4666AE" box="[918,1009,954,977]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Lasiurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has been the focus of numerous studies, and there is persistent controversy as to whether three genera (
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD568FC1EFB01616C" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1870" box="[1107,1206,1020,1043]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Aeorestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD568FC1EFB01616C" box="[1107,1206,1020,1043]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Aeorestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD397FBFFFC92614B" box="[684,805,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Dasypterus</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD252FBFFFC71614B" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[873,966,1053,1076]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD252FBFFFC71614B" box="[873,966,1053,1076]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Lasiurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), two genera (
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD554FBFFFD56612A" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Dasypterus</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD22DFBDCFCC5612A" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[790,882,1086,1109]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD22DFBDCFCC5612A" box="[790,882,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Lasiurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), or only one genus (
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD56CFBDCFB04612A" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[1111,1203,1086,1109]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD56CFBDCFB04612A" box="[1111,1203,1086,1109]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Lasiurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) should be recognized (Allen, 1894; Miller, 1907; Tate, 1942; Handley, 1960; Hoofer and Van Den Bussche, 2003; Roehrs et al., 2010; Baird et al., 2015, 2017; Ziegler et al., 2016). Recently, Baird et al. (2015, 2017) argued for recognition of three genera based on analyses of genetic data indicating reciprocal monophyly. In contrast, Ziegler et al. (2016) and Novaes et al. (2018) argued that taxonomic stability was better served by treating 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD397FA6AFCB860E0" authorityName="Fitzinger" authorityYear="1870" box="[684,783,1416,1439]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Aeorestes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD397FA6AFCB860E0" box="[684,783,1416,1439]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Aeorestes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD270FA6BFC7360DF" box="[843,964,1417,1440]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Dasypterus</emphasis>
as subgenera of 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD5BDFA6BFD6B60BE" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD5BDFA6BFD6B60BE" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Lasiurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. We concur with the latter authors and use 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD397FA29FCBF609D" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[684,776,1483,1506]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD397FA29FCBF609D" box="[684,776,1483,1506]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Lasiurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as the generic name for all these taxa. Thus defined, 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375698FF2DD27EFA0EFC16637C" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[837,929,1516,1539]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="132" pageNumber="132" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65698FF2DD27EFA0EFC16637C" box="[837,929,1516,1539]" italics="true" pageId="132" pageNumber="132">Lasiurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
includes 19 currently recognized species that can be distinguished from members of other vespertilionid genera by having long, dense fur covering the proximal third or more of the upper surface of the uropatagium; a short, deep rostrum; one pair of upper incisors; and right and left premaxillae separated by a palatal emargination that is approximately onethird the distance across the canines (Gardner and Handley, 2008; López-Baucells et al., 2018; Simmons and Cirranello, 2020).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7DEE653F5699FF2CD1B7FE84FEBB67F9" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" type="description">
<paragraph id="354B36B45699FF2CD1B7FE84FEBB67F9" blockId="133.[108,636,226,646]" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">
During the 2012 CEBIO bat course, two acoustic forms of 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375699FF2CD00DFE6AFE2564E0" authorityName="Gray" authorityYear="1831" box="[310,402,392,415]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65699FF2CD00DFE6AFE2564E0" box="[310,402,392,415]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">Lasiurus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were detected (
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375699FF2CD37CFE6AFF7764BF" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65699FF2CD37CFE6AFF2B64BF" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">Lasiurus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375699FF2CD1CEFE4BFECB64BF" box="[245,380,424,448]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="blossevillii">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65699FF2CD1CEFE4BFEB464BF" box="[245,259,425,448]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0780EAA65699FF2CD02BFE4AFECB64BF" box="[272,380,424,448]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">blossevillii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Based on range maps, only 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375699FF2CD193FE28FE8E649E" box="[168,313,457,481]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="blossevillii">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65699FF2CD193FE28FF01649E" box="[168,182,458,481]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">L</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="0780EAA65699FF2CD1F2FE2BFE8E649E" box="[201,313,457,481]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">blossevillii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375699FF2CD041FE28FE08649E" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[378,447,458,481]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ega">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65699FF2CD041FE28FE08649E" box="[378,447,458,481]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">L. ega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are expected to occur in the Yavarí-Ucayali interfluve (Gardner and Handley, 2008). Because we captured 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375699FF2CD307FDEEFDCB675C" baseAuthorityName="Gervais" baseAuthorityYear="1856" box="[572,636,524,547]" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Lasiurus" kingdom="Plantae" order="Poales" pageId="133" pageNumber="133" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ega">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65699FF2CD307FDEEFDCB675C" box="[572,636,524,547]" italics="true" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">L. ega</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at El Chino Village, the unidentified calls detected at Jenaro 
<collectingRegion id="F730F8565699FF2CD001FDACFE38671A" box="[314,399,590,613]" country="Panama" name="Herrera" pageId="133" pageNumber="133">Herrera</collectingRegion>
most likely belonged to this species.
</paragraph>
